    "import spacy\n",
    "import asent\n",
    "\n",
    "def load_speech():\n",
    "    file_path = \"trump_speech.txt\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    with open(file_path, \"r\") as f:\n",
    "        speech = f.read()\n",
    "\n",
    "    return speech\n",
    "\n",
    "speech = load_speech()"
   ]

   "source": [
    "# create spacy pipeline:\n",
    "nlp = spacy.blank(\"en\")\n",
    "nlp.add_pipe(\"sentencizer\")\n",
    "nlp.add_pipe(\"asent_en_v1\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "doc = nlp(speech)  # process document\n",
    "sentences = [sent for sent in doc.sents]  # extract sentences"
   ]

    "Already here we get quite a lot of information? Which opens up for a bunch of questions:\n",

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Extracting polarities\n",
    "\n",
    "To extract the polarity from a sentence we can simply use the `._.polarity` attribute to get teh polarity of the sentence:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "SpanPolarityOutput(neg=0.076, neu=0.853, pos=0.071, compound=-0.024, span=As President, my highest and most solemn duty is the defense of our nation and its citizens.\n",
       "\n",
       ")"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 10,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sentences[2]._.polarity"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Then assuming we want the compound (average) polarity we can simply extract it as so:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "-0.024005576936002263"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 9,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# extracting polarity from one sentence:\n",
    "compound_polarity = sentences[2]._.polarity.compound\n",
    "compound_polarity"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "For all the documents we can thus do:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 33,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Polarity pr. sentence\n",
    "polarities = [sent._.polarity.compound for sent in sentences]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
